question: Guá-ê gí-giân ēng `[☉1]` ê piáu-chù ê chi̍t-kang ê miâ, kap ēng `[♄1]` ê piáu-chù ê chi̍t-lé-pài ê miâ?
Kètsûn sié guók-gí ê miâ, i ê Thues-theh tōa-jī sē-khí-lâi sī 'T' ê lóng-tsóng sòo-liōng?
Na-ge ji̍t-ch Hun ê la̍k-ji̍t ê sî-chūn, chiah-ê bûn-jī kah `[♀...]` (sò͘-jī) ū siōng chē gí-giân ê koan-liân?
Chiah-sé liám-chiuⁿ chi̍t-ji̍t hō-chòe "tē-it" ê gí-giân, liáu-āu chhiáⁿ chiong hit jī-giân êléng-chiáⁿ-ji̍t ê sû kā chhut-lâi.
Tùi Pherisan gí-giân ê lē-pài-gō͘ kàu lē-pài-liáu ê miâ-chheng hong-sek lâi hun-sek. I chai̍t-ê chū-chek ê lu̍t-têng sī siáⁿ-mi̍h?
answer: Pherisan gí-giân sī chiap-jīm chū Lē-pài-ji̍t khai-sí ê chi̍t-ê bêng-liâⁿ ê sò͘-chek sòaⁿ-pâi. Lē-pài-ji̍t sī 'yekshanbe' (chi̍t-shanbe). Kè-jīm, Lē-pài-it sī 'doshanbe' (sò͘-shanbe), Lē-pài-jī sī 'seshanbe' (saⁿ-shanbe), chi̍t-ê 'chahârshanbe' (sì-shanbe), hō͘-lâng khoàⁿ-kîⁿ chi̍t-ê kiên-tāi ê hong-sek, iû chi̍t-ê sò͘-chek chiàⁿ-thâu liân-kòe "shanbe" chit-ê jī ê ki-chhú.

question: Tī chit ê lia̍t-toaⁿ lāi-bīn, ū kúi-ūi gín-á ê miâ-chheng ē ū chham-á 'sab', 'shab', he̍k-chiá 'sabt' ê jī?
Pōe-tōe gāi ʻIe-lân-gí ê sû “dagur” (lú-bīn ê ì-gú sī “ji̍t”), thè-ōaⁿ chò “deň” ê sî, Lāi-sa̍t-ji̍t ê sin miâ ē-sī siáⁿ mi̍h?
Tī chē-ko gí-giân lāi-bīn, ū chha-put tah chhiⁿ-chhiūⁿ chòe-lé-pài-la̍t (Saturday) ê miâ sī tùi 'Sabbath' lâi ê, koh ū chha-put tah chòe-lé-pài-gō͘ (Friday) ê miâ sī tùi 'Jum'ah'/'Gimgħa' lâi ê bô?
answer: Ū. Tī chi̍t kóa gí-giân lāi-bīn, chhián-ba̍t khòaⁿ-tit chi̍t ê tōa ê koan-liân. Lāi-bīn ū Arabic, Maltese, Malay, Indonesian, kap Sundanese, in lóng kā chòe-lé-pài-gō͘ ê miâ lâi chòe 'Jum'ah' (chi̍p-ha̍p ê kang) lâi khòaⁿ-tōaⁿ, kap chòe-lé-pài-la̍t ê miâ sī tùi 'Sabt' (Sabbath) lâi ê. Chit ê hong-sek sī chiap-chhiok tio̍h chi̍t koá bûn-hòa he̍k gí-giân ê éng-hióng, kài-sī tùi Arabic lâi ê, chòe liáu chi̍t lé-pài ê bóe-á ê miâ hong-bīn.

question: Amharic 腔 ê 禮拜幾名 (亲像 礼拜五 ('日頭落山') kah 礼拜六 ('第一个')) kah 别种 ê 辰光 拢真毋捌。表中，别个哪一号语言 ê 礼拜幾名，会使讲是毋捌，毋过毋是讲神话、数字抑是寻常宗教名词？
Koh ē tâi hō-miâ hō-chò chi̍t kò thiⁿ (khòaⁿ bu̍t-su-sut ), ū siá ēng hâu-chhat-á phiah ê anotation siōng-chió ê?
In which languages, the word for Saturday is 'Shabbat' or something similar?
